==Getting Started==

<p>Chat tab is an enhancement of the remote attack function by niknah in his kingdoms of camelot attack helper. Therefore for this feature to work correctly, make sure that any kocattack help by niknah or other scripts with this function are *disabled*.
<p>This is the current tab layout as of version 20110804a.
<p align="center"><img src="http://koc-power-bot.googlecode.com/files/Chat-setup.jpg" width="755" height="253">

<p>*Enable chat functions* - When checked will start monitoring chat for requests
<p>*Enable password* - When enabled will check if the correct password is given
<p>*Password field* - This is where you type in your password. As with all passwords, it is case-sensitive.
<p>*Allowed players* - Type in the names of players you want to give permission to your info. *Note* Each player's name goes on a separate line and the player's name are case sensitive, do not add a space after the players name.

<br>
==Usage==
<p>Example shown here is for unit count
<p>To use type /player command?password    *(Note that there is no space on either side of the question mark)*
<p align="center"><img src="http://koc-power-bot.googlecode.com/files/chat-question.jpg" width="300" height="54">
<p>For this example, type /Dragonsdeath units?polywantsacracker

<p>And if all permissions are correct you'll get this reply
<p align="center"><img src="http://koc-power-bot.googlecode.com/files/chat-answer.jpg" width="300" height="343">
<p>*Chat tab will only search for queries in whisper boxes.*
<p>*Also note that the table format is view-able in alliance chat tab. You will get a bunch of code if you view it in global tab*

<br>
==Commands==
<p>1) *units* - To get total troop count in all cities
<p>2) *attacks* - To get list of incoming attacks

